491245691.text: "High glucose also induces loss of the initiator caspase-9 and increases caspase-3 cleavage, effects blocked by IGF-I, suggesting that IGF-I prevents apoptosis in DRG neurons by regulating PI3K and Akt pathway effectors, including GSK-3beta, CREB, and FKHR, and by blocking caspase activation."
